TLE Error stands for Time Limit Exceeded Error. It is a runtime verdict issued by online coding judges which
indicate that your program takes too long to execute and failed to execute in limited timeframe. TLE does not mean your
code has bad logic or produces wrong answer. It simple means your
code is too slow to handle the problem larger test input.
Why TLE occur?
Inefficient Time Complexity - Using slow, brute-force approach like o(N2) nested loop when the problem constraints require an
O(n) or o(nlogn) approch.

Infinite Loops - A bug in your loop condition prevents the code form terminating.

Slow Input/Output - Standard print and read function can bottleneck your code when processing millions of lines of data.

Redundant Operation - Repeatedly recalculating the same value or copying massive objects inside a loop.
